hello lovelies thanks for joining me
tell me about your day

summary: I love that they never flaunt “shiny”, “polished” lifestyles even though they are undoubtedly successful. They seem quite humble...
question: I love that they never flaunt “shiny”, “polished” lifestyles even though they are undoubtedly successful. They seem quite humble with the way they live with occasional indulgences but overall I love how their content is pure CONTENT and never treated as opportunities to depict a certain lifestyle. In fact they seem pretty closed about their private life which I think is fantastic as it shows they’re not using that for attention and you know, over-sharing IS a thing.
answer:
oooh i agree completely, anon. dnp have money. i mean serious serious money. they could so very easily go all out, flash a rich lifestyle and brag about what they have.

but it comes down to this: they are genuine and good people. they both came from humble beginnings and haven’t lost touch with their roots and realities. the closest thing to ‘flashy’ about their lifestyles is dan’s love for way-too-expensive clothes, but the only reason i even know it’s expensive is because of the phandom fbi, he doesn’t tell us these things

they don’t try to turn their content into this ‘oh hey look how great our lives are!’ show, they do what they love because they love doing it. and even the times we could theoretically see a more flashy lifestyle, it’s blatantly obvious that they don’t actually live a crazy lavish life - they have an ordinary flat with ordinary things and they eat ordinary food and do ordinary stuff most of the time. 

i think this ties in really well with the concept of their tour: they’re just two normal guys who followed their passions and worked hard and got lucky, but it didn’t change who they are

mmmmm oversharing, interesting point :) i quite agree, it is, and there’s a lot to be said for them choosing not to overshare certain aspects of their life for that exact point: they want their content to be about their content. not about the peripheral aspects of their lives.

tell me what you love about dan and/or phil
